Resource Profile: DDCC:VS Add Bundle

Defining URL:http://worldhealthorganization.github.io/ddcc/StructureDefinition/DDCCVSAddBundle
Version:1.0.0
Name:DDCCVSAddBundle
Title:DDCC:VS Add Bundle
Status:Active as of 2022-11-23 04:25:10+0000
Definition:

Bundle to be transformed to from the DDCC:VS QuestionnaireResponse to add on the DDCC generator.

Publisher:WHO
Source Resource:XML / JSON / Turtle

The official URL for this profile is: 

http://worldhealthorganization.github.io/ddcc/StructureDefinition/DDCCVSAddBundle

IdGradePath(s)DetailsRequirements
bdl-5errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:ddccQR, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference, Bundle.entry:ddccCompositionmust be a resource unless there's a request or response
: resource.exists() or request.exists() or response.exists()
bdl-8errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:ddccQR, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference, Bundle.entry:ddccCompositionfullUrl cannot be a version specific reference
: fullUrl.contains('/_history/').not()
dom-2errorBundle.entry:ddccQR.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccPatient.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunization.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccComposition.resourceIf the resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT contain nested Resources
: contained.contained.empty()
dom-3errorBundle.entry:ddccQR.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccPatient.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunization.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccComposition.resourceIf the resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL be referred to from elsewhere in the resource or SHALL refer to the containing resource
: contained.where((('#'+id in (%resource.descendants().reference | %resource.descendants().as(canonical) | %resource.descendants().as(uri) | %resource.descendants().as(url))) or descendants().where(reference = '#').exists() or descendants().where(as(canonical) = '#').exists() or descendants().where(as(canonical) = '#').exists()).not()).trace('unmatched', id).empty()
dom-4errorBundle.entry:ddccQR.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccPatient.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunization.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccComposition.resourceIf a resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT have a meta.versionId or a meta.lastUpdated
: contained.meta.versionId.empty() and contained.meta.lastUpdated.empty()
dom-5errorBundle.entry:ddccQR.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccPatient.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunization.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccComposition.resourceIf a resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT have a security label
: contained.meta.security.empty()
dom-6best practiceBundle.entry:ddccQR.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccPatient.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunization.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccImmunizationRecommendation.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccDocumentReference.resource, Bundle.entry:ddccComposition.resourceA resource should have narrative for robust management
: text.`div`.exists()
ele-1error**ALL** elementsAll FHIR elements must have a @value or children
: hasValue() or (children().count() > id.count())
ext-1error**ALL** extensionsMust have either extensions or value[x], not both
: extension.exists() != value.exists()
sdcqr-1best practiceBundle.entry:ddccQR.resourceSubject SHOULD be present (searching is difficult without subject). Almost all QuestionnaireResponses should be with respect to some sort of subject.
: subject.exists()
sdcqr-2best practiceBundle.entry:ddccQR.resourceWhen repeats=true for a group, it'll be represented with multiple items with the same linkId in the QuestionnaireResponse. For a question, it'll be represented by a single item with that linkId with multiple answers.
: (QuestionnaireResponse|repeat(answer|item)).select(item.where(answer.value.exists()).linkId.isDistinct()).allTrue()
